Kotak Mahindra Bank manager took ?1.5 cr to convert ?35 cr.
The manager of the Kotak Mahindra Bank branch on Kasturba Gandhi Marg was remanded in five-day custody of the Enforcement Directorate today by a Delhi district court in Saket.The agency had arrested the manager in connection with cases on hawala trader Paras Mal Lodha and Delhi-based lawyer Rohit Tandon. The bank branch came under the Income Tax department scanner in connection with two suspicious accounts. Earlier, the I-T officials found several fake accounts with huge deposits in Axis Bank branches.ALSO READ: Delhi: 9 fake Kotak Mahindra Bank accounts with cash worth Rs 34 crore seizedÂ  